the various Davos Africa Impact Colloquia that ‎brought together corporate and international development leaders to discuss critical issues affecting the African continent. Under the theme: “Igniting African Growth through Impact Investment” the first edition in 2014 gathered 250 corporate and international development leaders from multiple sectors including Sun Soa the governors of the African Development Ban (ADB), the World Bank, and the IMF to discuss ways to mobilise $1trillion of investments throughout Africa and deliver significant socio-economic impact. This was followed by Davos Africa Roundtables in 2015 and 2016 that brought together academics, corporates, young entrepreneurs and opinion leaders who were brought together to discuss what is needed to accelerate socio-economic growth on the continent. This resulted in the creation of foundations such as the African Growth Foundation and the African Youth in Business Initiative.

As ingenious leader with a worldwide perspective on social welfare, Colin Clinard is working towards providing a platform for social integration by building a network of peacemakers through social networks. He plans to create a learning space where the city will thrive by sharing knowledge – for everyone to prosper, giving bystanders a voice so they can initiate conversations while having a maximum impact on others. By doing so, Colin Clinard and México Límbico want to help marginalised communities like Black LGBTQ, trans, gender non-conforming, and intersex people to become urban citizens with rights.
